{
  "stem": "14613.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I could give you-- and I am projecting myself right now, what I knew when I was living there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because today, what you know is completely different than what the perception was when we were in ghetto.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I have to go back and tell you what we thought, and what I thought.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The perception was that, at the beginning, Rumkowski thought that by keeping the ghetto together, and keeping the Jews confined there and working for the Germans, the thought was that maybe he will be able to save the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And this is one of the reasons why, at the very beginning, he took the children to school.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He wanted them to study.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "As, however, the condition changed, the perception changed, too.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The situation in ghetto became such that there was a great disparity between the so-called what you asked, the administration and the common man.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The Judenrat, and they called it [NON-ENGLISH], which was the leadership that were getting a lot of food, a lot of privileges, while the common man had very little to eat, and they were starving.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that the-- the antagonism between the administration-- and there were maybe a few types of administrations, because there was the administration as such, then there was the police, which was a different-- a different part of the organization or administration.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The resentments against the [NON-ENGLISH], the leadership, the resentments against the police-- which was completely independent, really, it was a Jewish police not accompanied by the Germans-- became more and more.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And as time progressed, the-- the problem started that you had aussiedlungs, you had people that were being sent out from ghetto.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You had old people, young people.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
